was picking it up, okay?

35:17.266 --> 35:18.734
So--
- Didn't you bring it with you?

35:18.767 --> 35:20.633
- Of course I did,
'cause Thomas said

35:20.633 --> 35:22.233
"Just in case they don't--

35:22.233 --> 35:24.266
I don't want you
to look like an idiot."

35:24.266 --> 35:26.133
- You're a girl that's been
dating this guy for two months.

35:26.166 --> 35:27.734
You just spent
ten grand on his credit card.

35:27.767 --> 35:29.066
Like, you could have put
two and two together,

35:29.100 --> 35:30.467
how that would have looked.

35:30.500 --> 35:31.600
- Well, and then I was gonna
return it tomorr--

35:31.633 --> 35:32.600
the next day, Craig.

35:32.633 --> 35:34.100
- Did you return it?

35:34.133 --> 35:35.667
- No, 'cause Thomas
said "You deserve it.

35:35.700 --> 35:37.200
"You've earned it and Patricia--

35:37.233 --> 35:39.533
if Patricia loved it,
then I love it."

35:39.567 --> 35:41.000
- How did you earn it?
- So I don't like that you're--

35:41.033 --> 35:42.467
- What does that mean?

35:42.500 --> 35:44.333
- I've never seen Thomas--
he's so frugal.

35:44.367 --> 35:46.400
As, like, nice of a house
he lives in

35:46.400 --> 35:49.266
and as nice as he dresses,
he's a very frugal person.

35:49.300 --> 35:51.066
- Maybe with you, Kathryn.

35:51.100 --> 35:53.266
- Oh, okay.
- Yeah, maybe just with you.

35:53.266 --> 35:54.400
- Wow.
- No.

35:54.400 --> 35:56.100
Maybe with--yeah.
- Okay.

35:56.133 --> 35:59.066
I guess I wasn't deserving
of the nice things, huh?

35:59.100 --> 36:00.200
- Well, he did give you
two children,

36:00.233 --> 36:01.633
so he gave you something.
Yeah.

36:01.667 --> 36:03.533
- I didn't give him
the children, lovely.

36:03.567 --> 36:05.133
This is all making sense.
- You got two kids.

36:05.166 --> 36:07.166
- You're just so... [muttering]
I can't.

36:07.166 --> 36:09.166
- Patricia was really
a mentor to you

36:09.200 --> 36:11.100
and she was rooting
for your relationship

36:11.133 --> 36:13.000
throughout the season.
- Yes.

36:13.033 --> 36:15.166
- What's your relationship
with her now?

36:15.200 --> 36:17.166
- There's no relationship
with her.

36:17.200 --> 36:18.300
- What happened?

36:18.300 --> 36:20.433
- She was inciting me to go

36:20.467 --> 36:21.767
against you, Kathryn.

36:22.000 --> 36:23.300
- What does that mean?

36:23.333 --> 36:25.166
- She asked me how
Thomas and I were doing.

36:25.200 --> 36:26.567
And I said great.
And she says, "Good."

36:26.567 --> 36:28.166
She goes, "It might be
kind of selfish, but

36:28.200 --> 36:30.667
"I want to see you guys together
just for the fact

36:30.700 --> 36:33.433
that Kathryn can't
try to get him back," okay?

36:33.433 --> 36:36.400
I--[stammers]
my one biggest regret--

36:36.433 --> 36:38.133
can you look at me
when I'm talking to you?

36:38.166 --> 36:40.100
- Oh, yeah, sorry.
Distracted.

36:40.133 --> 36:41.700
- My one biggest regret

36:41.700 --> 36:44.133
was going on that shopping trip
with her,

36:44.166 --> 36:45.700
when I should have
gone with you.

36:45.734 --> 36:47.066
- That's your...
- That's your biggest regret?

36:47.100 --> 36:49.133
- Biggest regret?

36:49.166 --> 36:50.400
- Yeah.

36:50.433 --> 36:51.734
- So if you could
change one thing,

36:51.767 --> 36:53.300
that's what you would change?
- Yeah.

36:53.333 --> 36:55.300
- What happened
between you and Patricia

36:55.333 --> 36:56.734
to turn it south?

36:56.734 --> 36:59.066
- Well, someone was
calling Thomas a lunatic.

36:59.066 --> 37:01.000
And everyone was pretty much
saying it's Kathryn.

37:01.033 --> 37:03.600
And when I realized
it was this other person...

37:03.600 --> 37:05.066
- Someone else.
- That she's familiar with...

37:05.066 --> 37:06.333
- Patricia?
- Yes.

37:06.367 --> 37:08.400
- I told Patricia,
Thomas is hurt.

37:08.433 --> 37:10.200
What do you
have to say about this?

37:10.233 --> 37:11.533
- This is on social media
you're talking about?

37:11.567 --> 37:13.166
- Yes.
- And then Patricia said?

37:13.200 --> 37:15.200
- Yes.
"Oh, you're crazy to think that.

37:15.200 --> 37:17.200
"Kathryn is this person.
She is this troll.

37:17.200 --> 37:19.133
"Here's this account.
Block this account.

37:19.166 --> 37:20.433
Here's the one--"
And I'm going--

37:20.467 --> 37:21.700
- This is all
about social media?

37:21.734 --> 37:23.200
- Oh, my God.
- Yes.

37:23.200 --> 37:24.533
This is how it started.
- Wait a second.

37:24.567 --> 37:26.667
I--I observed on social media
you and Thomas

37:26.700 --> 37:29.633
systematically sabotaging
your relationship with Patricia.

37:29.633 --> 37:31.233
- Yeah.
- With certain tweets.

37:31.233 --> 37:33.500
Thomas said, "Why don't you
go back to New York,

37:33.533 --> 37:35.500
Miss Queen of Southern
Gentility?" to Patricia.

37:35.533 --> 37:37.166
I was like...

37:37.200 --> 37:38.200
- So this is what
the falling out was about?

37:38.233 --> 37:39.633
- Correct.
- Okay.

37:39.667 --> 37:41.300
- Because someone wrote
some bad things about Thomas.

37:41.333 --> 37:43.300
I mean, Patricia's
not in charge of other people.

37:43.333 --> 37:46.066
And--and that--there goes
the bridge, torched.

37:46.100 --> 37:47.767
And, like, she had been
so good to him, man.

37:47.767 --> 37:49.166
- [mumbles]
- So Thomas is not--

37:49.200 --> 37:50.567
- In the face of
a lot of bullsh--.

37:50.600 --> 37:52.600
- So Thomas is not
speaking to Patricia?

37:52.633 --> 37:54.567
- Oh, no, it's over.

37:54.600 --> 37:56.600
[dramatic music]

37:56.633 --> 37:58.633
- Coming up...
- You're lucky you made it.

37:58.667 --> 38:00.233
- Ooh, are you
threatening me now?

38:00.233 --> 38:02.033
- No, I'm not.
- This is so interesting.

38:02.066 --> 38:03.500
- I think you're lucky because
it would have counted as...

38:03.500 --> 38:05.300
- Obviously.
- A fail if you didn't make it.

38:05.333 --> 38:06.600
- It's none of your
----ing business to begin with.

38:06.633 --> 38:07.600
- [indistinct]
So they stayed open for you.

38:07.633 --> 38:09.000
- You're a complete asshole.

38:12.400 --> 38:12.667
- Welcome back to

38:12.667 --> 38:13.300
- Welcome back to
the "Southern Charm" reunion.

38:15.400 --> 38:17.767
As if the Charleston waters
weren't choppy enough,

38:18.000 --> 38:19.667
the crew packed up
their battered bodies

38:19.667 --> 38:23.633
and emotional baggage
