- Small town.

1:02:03.767 --> 1:02:05.300
- You're not.
- Small town.

1:02:05.333 --> 1:02:06.567
- Craig, do you think
you and Naomie

1:02:06.600 --> 1:02:08.600
will be able
to maintain or build

1:02:08.633 --> 1:02:10.467
a friendship
now that she's moved on?

1:02:10.467 --> 1:02:11.667
- I mean, I hope so because--

1:02:11.700 --> 1:02:13.200
but I know what I said today.

1:02:13.233 --> 1:02:14.567
But, I mean, it's how I felt.

1:02:14.600 --> 1:02:16.066
But, obviously,
if I could go back,

1:02:16.100 --> 1:02:17.433
you know, I would
change everything.

1:02:17.467 --> 1:02:18.667
- Does that make you feel good,

1:02:18.700 --> 1:02:20.433
to hear he would
change everything?

1:02:20.467 --> 1:02:22.200
- [sighs]
I guess.

1:02:22.200 --> 1:02:24.400
I don't know,
I'm just asking you to respect

1:02:24.433 --> 1:02:28.000
my relationship
and be happy for me.

1:02:28.033 --> 1:02:31.567
- Shep, you've been a sounding
board to all of your friends,

1:02:31.600 --> 1:02:33.066
particularly Kathryn.

1:02:33.100 --> 1:02:34.767
Do you feel closer to her now

1:02:35.000 --> 1:02:36.233
at the end of the season?

1:02:36.233 --> 1:02:37.600
- I really do.

1:02:37.633 --> 1:02:39.333
And she knows that
whenever she needs anything,

1:02:39.367 --> 1:02:42.500
I'll drop whatever I'm doing
and, uh, help her out.

